 {"id":"rust_proxy-tkj","title":"Implement use_last degradation policy","description":"## Scope

Implement the use_last degradation policy that attempts connection through the most recently healthy proxy.

## Rationale

Transient failures are common. A proxy that was healthy recently is likely to work again soon. This policy provides a middle ground between fail_closed (too strict) and try_all (too slow).

## Implementation Details

### Track Last Healthy Proxy

Add to StateStore:

```rust
impl StateStore {
    /// Get the proxy ID that was most recently healthy
    pub async fn get_last_healthy_proxy(&self) -> Option<String> {
        let state = self.inner.read().await;

        state.proxies
            .iter()
            .filter_map(|(id, stats)| {
                stats.last_healthy.map(|ts| (id.clone(), ts))
            })
            .max_by_key(|(_, ts)| *ts)
            .map(|(id, _)| id)
    }
}
```

### Policy Implementation

```rust
pub async fn apply_use_last_policy(
    config: &AppConfig,
    state: &StateStore,
    target: &str,
) -> Result<(TcpStream, String)> {
    let last_healthy = state.get_last_healthy_proxy().await
        .ok_or_else(|| anyhow::anyhow!(
            "No proxy has ever been healthy (use_last policy)"
        ))?;

    tracing::warn!(
        proxy = %last_healthy,
        "Attempting last healthy proxy (use_last policy)"
    );

    let proxy = config.proxies
        .iter()
        .find(|p| p.id == last_healthy)
        .ok_or_else(|| anyhow::anyhow!(
            "Last healthy proxy '{}' no longer in config", last_healthy
        ))?;

    let stream = connect_through_proxy(proxy, target).await?;

    tracing::info!(
        proxy = %last_healthy,
        "Connection to last healthy proxy succeeded"
    );

    Ok((stream, last_healthy))
}
```

### Edge Cases

1. **No proxy ever healthy**: Fall back to fail_closed behavior
2. **Last healthy proxy removed from config**: Log warning, fall back
3. **Multiple proxies with same last_healthy time**: Pick by priority

### Fallback Chain

Consider making use_last fall back to try_all on failure:

```rust
match apply_use_last_policy(config, state, target).await {
    Ok(result) => Ok(result),
    Err(e) => {
        tracing::debug!(error = %e, "use_last failed, falling back to try_all");
        apply_try_all_policy(config, target).await
    }
}
```

This is configurable: some users want strict use_last (fail if it fails), others want use_last-then-try_all.

## Acceptance Criteria

- Identifies most recently healthy proxy correctly
- Attempts connection through that proxy
- Clear logging of policy application
